An eThekwini metro police officer, Constable Ndumiso Khumalo appeared in the Umzimkhulu magistrate's court over the alleged murder of his ex-girlfriend, Zinhle Muthwa. DURBAN - An eThekwini metro police officer accused of murdering his ex-girlfriend will remain behind bars. Zinhle Muthwa’s body was found on New Year’s Day with a gunshot wound to the head. Ndumiso Khumalo has abandoned his bail application. READ: Five facts: Femicide in South Africa The State had previously said it would oppose bail. Family and friends of the victim welcomed the move. The matter will resume on 7 February, pending a decision by the Chief Justice to move the case to another court.